Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 10:37:32 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?fman/pcd:=20PR14z=20=E2=80=94=20set=20hmct=5Fus?=
 =?UTF-8?q?ed=20in=20v1.2=20OH-port-chain=20encoders?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Patch 0036 introduced fman_pcd_manip_chain_create() with a precondition
that each contained manip carry a non-zero hmct_used recording the
exact byte count of its HMCT command stream.  0036 added hmct_used
assignments to the four v1.1 encoders (NAT_V4, NAT_V6, VLAN_PUSH,
VLAN_POP) but missed the four v1.2 encoders introduced by patch 0033
(TTL_DEC rewrite, RMV_ETHERNET, INSRT_GENERIC,
FIELD_UPDATE_IPV4_FORWARD).  Result on live mono LS1046A: every call
to fman_pcd_manip_chain_create() from ask.ko's ask_hw_flow_insert_v4_tcp()
returns -EINVAL at the per-source-manip hmct_used==0 validation arm,
so every offloaded flow falls back to SW and the M2 gate measures
6.796 Gbps / 68.67 % CPU instead of the >= 2 Gbps / <= 5 % CPU target.

Fix: set hmct_used in each of the four v1.2 encoders to the exact
number of bytes that encoder wrote into manip->hmct.

  TTL_DEC          1 cmd word              =>  hmct_used = 4
  RMV_ETHERNET     1 cmd word              =>  hmct_used = 4
  INSRT_GENERIC    1 cmd + ceil(size/4) words => 4 + n_words*4
  IPV4_FORWARD     1 cmd + 0..1 DSCP words =>  emit_payload ? 8 : 4

Native ARM64 build clean (Cobalt 100, kernel 6.18.29).
M2 gate re-run pending on dispatched ISO build.

Signed-off-by: Build Cobalt100 <build@cobalt100>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c
index 06f64b7..62c9eea 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c
@@ -602,6 +602,7 @@ cmd |= FMAN_PCD_HMCD_IPV4_UPDATE_TTL;
 
 iowrite32be(cmd, hmct);
 
+manip->hmct_used = 4; /* PR14z: cmd word, no payload */
 *out_op = FMAN_PCD_HMAN_OC_IP_MANIP;
 return hmct;
 }
@@ -637,6 +638,7 @@ cmd |= (u32)FMAN_PCD_L2_HDR_RMV_SIZE
 
 iowrite32be(cmd, hmct);
 
+manip->hmct_used = 4; /* PR14z: cmd word, no payload */
 *out_op = FMAN_PCD_HMAN_OC;
 return hmct;
 }
@@ -701,6 +703,7 @@ iowrite32be(word, cur);
 cur += 4;
 }
 
+manip->hmct_used = 4 + (n_words * 4); /* PR14z: cmd word + payload words */
 *out_op = FMAN_PCD_HMAN_OC;
 return hmct;
 }
@@ -763,6 +766,7 @@ payload = ((u32)p->ipv4_forward.new_dscp)
 iowrite32be(payload, hmct + 4);
 }
 
+manip->hmct_used = emit_payload ? 8 : 4; /* PR14z: cmd + optional DSCP word */
 *out_op = FMAN_PCD_HMAN_OC_IP_MANIP;
 return hmct;
 }
